text:
Terrible Experience – Rude Staff and Unwelcoming Atmosphere

name: Rachel Swaby
text:
5-Star Review

Roots Lebanese Restaurant in Streatham is, without a doubt, the best Lebanese dining experience in the area! The mixed grill was an absolute standout – perfectly cooked, rich in flavour, and beautifully presented. Each dish was a testament to authentic Lebanese cuisine done right.

What truly sets Roots apart is the outstanding team. The staff were warm, attentive, and genuinely passionate about ensuring we had the best possible experience. They went above and beyond to make us feel welcome, catering to every detail with a smile.

A special shoutout to Charles, the owner, who exemplifies excellence in hospitality. His commitment to quality and personal attention to each guest is remarkable. Charles’ warm demeanor and hands-on approach create an atmosphere that feels both professional and family-like.

If you’re looking for unbeatable Lebanese food paired with exceptional service, Roots is the clear winner in Streatham. This place is a true gem, and I can’t wait to return!C’est

The capaccino was absolutely perfect and the cocoa on top was rich and chocolaty exactly how it should be. The food came out quickly and every mouthful was honestly so deliciously and vibrantly filled with flavour including the salad! The baklava after food went well with my capaccino! You can tell they care about their customers, the food and service. Even the toilets were so clean and pretty! I will be coming back!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Roots and it was an unforgettable experience from start to finish. This charming family-run restaurant offers a warm, welcoming atmosphere that makes you feel right at home the moment you step through the door.

The food is nothing short of spectacular. Every dish we tried was bursting with flavour, beautifully presented, and made with the freshest ingredients. It’s clear that the family takes great pride in their culinary creations, and their passion for food shines through in every bite.

The service was impeccable—attentive, friendly, and genuinely caring. The family members running the restaurant made us feel like part of their family, sharing stories and recommendations that enhanced our dining experience.

From the cozy ambiance to the exceptional food and outstanding service, Roots is a true gem. I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience. Five stars all the way!

Last weekend, we had the pleasure of celebrating my sister's baby shower at Roots, and it was an unforgettable experience. From the moment we walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting, perfectly setting the tone for our special occasion.
The staff at Roots truly went above and beyond to make our celebration exceptional. They were attentive, accommodating, and genuinely seemed to care about making our event memorable. From helping us with decorations to ensuring that every guest was comfortable, their service was impeccable.

The food at Roots was nothing short of spectacular. Each dish was thoughtfully prepared with fresh, local ingredients, showcasing the restaurant's commitment to quality and sustainability. We particularly enjoyed the Fattoush salads and the beautifully presented entrees. The flavors were vibrant, and the portions were generous, satisfying all our guests.
The highlight of the evening was the dessert, which included an array of delicious cream and a tasty chocolate cake that was as delicious as it was beautiful. The staff even surprised us with a special congratulatory message for my sister, adding a personal touch that made the event even more special.

Roots is not just a restaurant; it’s a place where memories are made. Whether you're celebrating a special occasion or simply enjoying a night out, Roots provides an exceptional dining experience with its outstanding service, delightful ambiance, and exquisite cuisine.
We left with full hearts and satisfied appetites, grateful for the wonderful time we had. Thank you, Roots, for making my sister's baby shower an event to remember. We will definitely be back!
Thank you, Charles!

text:
Absolutely outstanding experience at Roots Restaurant in Streatham! From the moment we contacted the restaurant, we were impressed by the warm and friendly customer service. Charles, the owner, went above and beyond to ensure our dining experience was memorable.

Upon visiting the restaurant, Charles welcomed us with open arms and even treated us to a taste of his delicious food. We were immediately sold on booking our event there. Charles kept in touch leading up to the party, providing reassurance and ensuring everything was in place.

The day of the party exceeded our expectations. The food was exceptional - freshly made and perfectly seasoned. Even our picky eaters were delighted with the variety of choices on the party menu. The portion sizes were generous, and every dish was a hit.

A special mention to Charles and the staff for their impeccable service. They made the birthday celebration extra special by playing Stevie Wonder's "Happy Birthday" song as the cake arrived. It's clear that Roots is a family business with a passion for serving their customers.

We highly recommend Roots Restaurant to anyone looking for an exceptional dining experience. Thank you, Charles, and the entire team, for making our event unforgettable. We'll definitely be returning soon!

name: Sam “SJ” McCarthy
text:
Alright hear me now, this is a quick and snappy food review just some acknowledgment for this Lebanese grill in streatham hill called Roots. Beautiful interior, definitely aesthetically pleasing enough if you want to go here for a quick birthday lunch. Beautiful but simplistic food which you can’t go wrong with. I got the mixed grill which was £17.25 so not too expensive.

Shish Taouk
Which is basically seasoned chicken cubes. Most of the chicken cubes were succulent, seasoned well but a bit salty, one was a bit dry but we can ignore it since it was an anomaly.

Lamb Kafta -  tender, flavoursome, meat that wasn’t overly seasoned so the taste of the meat it self was still present and the most prominent which I believe is the is the point. To let the real flavour of the meat to show through. Fantastic stuff !

Lamb skewers were also flavoured well, weren’t chewy which is always a risk with that particular type of meat. It was the best lamb skewer I’ve had in some time. Very enjoyable !

The season rice was just beautiful, delicate and a great side to all that meat and definitely well flavoured which is a continuous theme for this restaurant.

Overall rating 7.5/10

For more reviews check my insta sjtalks_

address: 110, 112 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BS, United Kingdom
name: Mark Matheson
text:
I am a lover of Shawarma, hugely, and have been for close to 16 years now and the one made here at Roots was as good as any that I’ve had elsewhere in London eg Marble Arch, Camberwell, Norbury and several other places.

But when you combine great food with funny, friendly and a warm service, then we know that food tastes so much better.

Roots’ food was like having a great meal at home cooked with love and laughter.

The Owner and his Daughter run an establishment that should be in the City with a 50% premium on their prices … but I’m so glad they’re not as they are just around the corner from me with prices for the ordinary folk.

Anyway, if they keep this wonderfully high standard of food going, they’ll have enough to open a new restaurant up town as well and keep Roots Streatham too hopefully.

If you’re reading this review then all I can say is it was worth every penny.

Deliciosos 👍🏾

It was enjoyable but not exceptional, making it a safe choice for a good lunch. While I don't think you'll be disappointed, I wouldn't suggest going in expecting to be too impressed. I will say that my aunt took me there as she loves their sea bass, and this time was no different for her, so if that sort of meal appeals to you, check Roots out!

name: Diane Brown
text:
I went to ROOTS as 2 of my friends spoke very highly of this labanese restaurant. I ordered a Mix Grill with wings as I heard their wings are very nice. The wings were absolutely delicious 👌🏽👌🏽👌🏽 as well as the rest of the meat. Everything was sizzling hot and everything had a nice taste. The pitter bread that came with the mix grill was nice and soft and had a nice little filling inside which contained onions.

I had a Roots passion fruit Martini cocktail which was really good. However there was no sign of a passion fruit inside my cocktail! 🤦🏽‍♀️😩. It looked like I had Fanta inside my cocktail glass with a few ice cubes lol 🤦🏽‍♀️. At £9.50 I would have expected my cocktail to look a bit more like a cocktail ☺️.

The customer service was good, and the lady even came back over to ask if our cocktail was ok & if we wanted another one.

Overall I was very impressed with the food. I will definitely be visiting again! I think ROOTS is a hidden gem in Streatham 😊. I would rate this place 9/10. The lady waiter has excellent customer service… 👌🏽

name: Antonia Barraclough
text: We got the set menu for 4, which included a variety of mezze starters, two mixed grills, a bottle of house wine and some baklava. One of us was a vegetarian who was offered moussaka or a okra stew as an alternative, but as he didn’t like those options we were offered an alternative option to choose a couple of sides instead at no extra cost which was very kind. We also had someone in our party who had a nut allergy and they were very attentive to this. It was ALOT of food, so well worth the cost in my opinion! The bottle of wine was upgraded and we also got a free Lebanese coffee at the end which was a nice touch! Lovely flavours (especially the lemony chicken wings), great friendly service, perhaps one of the best I’ve experienced in a long time in London, and really cool decor inside. Will be visiting again as we live so close!

Not to forget the shesha! Not to forget the great service of the staff and the very funny and engaging owner!  Great for vegetarians, pescatarians!

name: Asya Bear
text:
We stumbled along this place whilst trying to find a place to eat. We decided to go in as it was a new restaurant in Streatham.

We were greeted by the lovely waiter, who guided us to our seat. The menu had a large variety of Lebanese food which included hot mezzeh and cold mezzeh. I have some issues with food in general, and the chefs were very accommodating and met my requirements. I enjoyed my meal a lot. We were actually being served by the owner, who is a very lovely person.

After a few visits , we fell in love with their garden and decided to have my birthday party there!  Which ended up to be, the party of the season for all my family & friends! At the party we had 25 people plus parents , we had some cold platter mezzeh and the kids had chicken, rice, chips and salad. Everybody enjoyed it , including parents!

Overall, I recommend this place to everyone who wants to go there, the food is fantastic, the atmosphere is great, the owner is nice  and the service is wonderful.

address: 110, 112 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BS, United Kingdom
name: Ryhad Mahrez
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Mr Mahrez
We at Sahara care about our customers reviews … sorry if your visit wasn’t as you wished and that’s can be fixed .
Most importantly that’s you have enjoyed your falafel …
I would like to offer you the refund of £.090  and on the top of that we offer you 2 falafel wraps on the house …..
regarding if we are empty always I can tell you that’s we are not …
Kind regards
Charles
text:
I always try to support local businesses and thought I would give this place a try but never again. I ordered two falafel wraps at this place during my lunch break to take back home for my wife and I. When paying at the till I got asked if I wanted the lunch time deal of £5.95 which included a wrap and a drink. I politely declined as I just wanted a wrap. When paying for the wraps the guy at the till went to charge me for the £11.90 for the lunch time deal. I told him that I didn't want the deal and he then proceeded to "change" the amount to £11. As I paid for the wraps I got a notification that £11.90 was taken from my card. He never changed the amount.

The pure cheekines to gain just an extra 90p for a sale has cost this place a customer as I actually enjoyed the wrap. When I mentioned that he has still charged me for the extra he acted as if he had done nothing wrong and it is just ridiculous the extent people go to. Treat the customer fairly and they will return. I can now see why this place is always empty.

text: Looking for a mellow not over crowded stop to catch up & chill with a friend on an early Saturday evening. The place was perfect....food was fresh and great tasting, from the hummus & stuffed vine leaves, to the mains of juicy flavoursome chicken with sides with a super refreshing (well made) mojito!... The ambiance was spot on, that we stay on for many hour after, slowing tying late into the evening with an awesome hit of Lebanese coffee, baklava, and pots & pots if fresh mint tea to compliment the smok of a well lit shisha. The staff, were beyond attentive and welcoming, but super friendly, relaxed & prompt in service, which really made our visit really comfortable.  A big thank you especially to Charlie & Maha, who kindly kept our drinks & coal topped up to the very end, and the wonderful conversation and fun vibe they shared too....We most definitely will return!...

name: Jacqui Knight
text:
An Absolute Gem! Stumbled across this place quite by accident,  and so glad we did!
So many good things to say about this cafe, because it's so much more than just any old cafe,  this place was full of good vibes, with a right warm welcome!  The food was delicious and superb value for money,  much variety,  there's something for everybody here! must say the pizzas are superb, the vegetarian options plentiful and a great choice of meat dishes. The management/waiting staff made us feel very special, My only disappointment was my favoured Aubergine dish was unavailable,  but i see that as the perfect opportunity to go back!  Oh another big plus BYOB (bring your own booze) kerching! Everyone's a winner....
Some more pluses.... Shisha... (which will be on the menu next time) oh and the decor, how can you not like ther beautiful lanterns that adorn the place... Very much looking forward to my next visit, a place that I'd happily travel to from Maidstone for an evening out.
I wish the management and staff the very best through these unprecedented times. Make a point of going here,  you will not be disappointed! ❤🍆

responseFromOwnerText:
Dear M Meho
Allow me to help you with your start
You have been welcomed to our
Shisha garden and allowed to play
Cards where we don’t allow
Playing cards but as your 1st time
Visite We did.
Your food and hot drinks arrived within
Reasonable time ... shisha took A bit
Of time as tonight we had a problem
With lighter machine and shisha
Manger explained and was more
Then polite with you
Regarding your baklava
You have received 5 portions
Despite the offer clearly stated one
Per shisha . ( you ordered 2 )
And yet you stayed good 2 hours
Playing cards enjoying the shisha.
I would appreciate if you have mentioned your experience there and
Then so we could fixed your problem
But to leave the place with a big smile
And yet to write such a review
We find it that’s not fair.
We do care about our customers
And our 5 stars reviews our witness.
Looking forward seeing you back
To Sahara ....
kind regards
Charles

address: 110, 112 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BS, United Kingdom
name: Joanne Collins
text: After years of studying I finally completed my doctorate so wanted to do something special to celebrate.  About 30-35 of my friends came with me to this place and had a fabulous time.  We brought some alcohol as they don’t sell it.  The food was amazing and the portions were generous.  The decor is beautiful and the attention to detail in this place shows.  Attention to detail also came over in the customer care. Throughout  the evening Alex and the owner made sure we had all we needed.  Between us we had everything on the menu, meat, veg, fish.  I had lamb and loved it but now have to go back for the chicken and the sea bass!  We were there for over 4 hours (till closing) and there were no complaints from my guests.  I didn’t tell my guests about the belly dancer, I thought I’d let that be a surprise.  She was great, she engaged us and got a few to get up and dance with her. An amazing night for a special moment in my life.  Many of us are already making plans to return either for the lunch time offer or back in the evening or just whenever we can.    I highly recommend this place. ❤️*****

name: Ronete Cohen
text: The restaurant is very beautiful and comfortable and the food is delicious. The service is very friendly. I highly recommend the mezze: the stuffed vine leaves and the baba ganoush were the best I'd had in a long time. The hummus with avocado was divine.
title: Roots Restaurant

address: 110, 112 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BS, United Kingdom
name: Jigar Dalia
text: First time I came here on Friday and was surprised it wasn't busy at all but quite the opposite. This place is fairly new so it is understandable. The interior is great! They have a little fountain inside the restaurant as you walk past which is nice. Shisha prices range from £15 to £20. The range of flavours are decent for a new place but I am sure they will expand their list of flavours available the more busier it gets. They have a belly dancer who comes on Saturday evening around 9pm. (If you want a male belly dancer, ask the owner and he will wax his legs prior to dancing for you, however you must throw money at him - Monopoly money!!). They do show sports. They can improve on their heating as it is quite empty when we went and the place is slightly cold. They provide blankets on a positive note. They accept cash & card (no Amex). Parking wise - there is a residential streets which you can park after a certain time (maybe 6:30 onwards) but there is single yellow and red lines which you can park. The service is great, however I will come back when the place is busy to see how the service is. Food wise - Lebanese & halal. They do not serve alcohol but you can bring your own.

name: PzzzUp
text: Shisha was excellent and smoothie was delicious too, haven't tasted the food so cannot comment on that. Didn't see anything that particularly tickled my fancy. Location is decent. Parking is easy after 7. Atmosphere and venue is pretty nice with a North African/Arabic theme. Shisha garden looked cosy but was very cold. We are in December, the heaters didn't do a good job of warming the place. Staff were super friendly, soo helpful. Pricing I would say is definitely not cheap but still reasonable.

text: This is our new shisha spot! The setting is beautiful and decorated with detail. Stefano’s hospitality was elite - he frequently checked up on us, provided us with blankets in the cold and gave us complimentary baklava. They also offer food, desserts and drinks. We definitely recommend this unique social spot in Streatham.
